According to Choreo,

If thorough System Identification has been performed, the system‚Äôs MoI can be calculated from mass * trackwidth/2 * kA-Angular/kA-Linear, where trackwidth is the largest distance between the robot‚Äôs wheel centers‚Ä¶

However, the largest distance between the robot‚Äôs wheel centers is actually the drivebase diameter for swerve drives.
Why did Choreo choose to write trackwidth/2 rather than drivebase radius?
